# Scripts to create an Orin/Thor qSPI tarball for IGX's BMC.

      README                                        <-- this file
      bmcflashqspi.sh                               <-- final BMC running script included in tarball
      ../qspi_flash/kernel_flash_qspi.sh            <-- script inside downloaded rcm-boot initrd to flash IGX's qSPI
      l4t_generate_igx_qspi_for_bmcflash.sh orin    <-- script to build Orin qSPI tarball for IGX's BMC flash
      l4t_generate_igx_qspi_for_bmcflash.sh thor    <-- script to build Thor qSPI tarball for IGX's BMC flash

# Prerequisites:
      - x86-64 Linux build machine
      - NVIDIA Orin/Thor sample file system or user provided root file system
      - An ethernet connection to IGX's BMC for flashing


# Build the Orin/Thor qSPI tarball for BMC

This section explains how to build a BMC image and subsequent tarball. These steps must be completed
using a x86-64 linux build machine. The usb connection to Orin/Thor is not required for this process.

1. Download one of the following packages:
      - customer_release.tbz2
      - Jetson_Linux_<VERSION>_aarch64.tbz2

2. Install the BSP package.

3. After you installed customer_release.tbz2 or Jetson_Linux_<VERSION>_aarch64.tbz2:
      a. Install NVIDIA Orin/Thor sample file system to Linux_for_Tegra/rootfs.
      b. Go to the Linux_for_Tegra directory
      c. Enter the following commands:
           cd Linux_for_Tegra

           sudo ./tools/bmc_flash/l4t_generate_igx_qspi_for_bmcflash.sh orin|thor

           The script will create a tarball in
               generic_release_aarch64/Linux_for_Tegra/bmc_tegraflash_<VERSION>.tbz2


# Flash the Orin/Thor's qSPI image from IGX's BMC

This section explains how to copy the built tarball from the Linux build machine to the IGX's BMC
and run the BMC script to flash the Orin/Thor's qSPI flash memory.

1. Copy the tarball to the BMC
      scp generic_release_aarch64/Linux_for_Tegra/bmc_tegraflash_<VERSION>.tbz2 root@<bmc_ip>:/run/initramfs

2. Log into the BMC with its credentials
      ssh root@<bmc_ip>

3. Untar the tarball
      cd /run/initramfs
      tar -xvf bmc_tegraflash_<VERSION>.tbz2

4. Flash the Orin/Thor qSPI image from the BMC
      bmcflash/bmcflashqspi.sh

Note:
1. Please replace <bmc_ip> with the IP address actually assigned to BMC(For example,192.168.1.110).
2. Replace <VERSION> with the actual version number of the Orin/Thor release(for exmaple, R36.2.0).
